"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The method `ax.set_xticks` expects the positions of the ticks, not the actual date values. The `df.date.unique()` returns an array of datetime objects, which is not suitable for `ax.set_xticks`. Instead, you should use the positions of the ticks, which can be obtained using `ax.get_xticks()`. Additionally, `ax.set_xticklabels` should be used with the formatted date strings.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19,20\\n<ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n<ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n>ax.set_xticks(ax.get_xticks())\\n>ax.set_xticklabels(labels=[date.strftime('%Y-%m-%d') for date in df.date.unique()], rotation=45)\"\n}"